So the chonky edition arrived. While the embossed Gundam is nice, the white text elsewhere is horrendous. The printing leaves a lot to be desired and they look incredibly fuzzy/blurry. Also, the blue print of the cover rubs off fingers and on the white text, so beware while handling. Weighs 6.1lbs.

Print quality isn't the best compared to the smaller Vertical release  Yas' watercolors are a bit more muted and some detail is lost unlike the glossy edition. There's more weird cropping because of the enlarged size, because the bleed lines were different in these.

Doesn't detract, but it's noticeable if you've followed both editions. Stitching is kinda iffy, too. I feel like any good read of this and pages will pop out. It's almost too big. Given the larger size, they should've tweaked the lettering because it's still as bad in spots as before.

It's a beast of a book. Color sections are retained, but I can't see how this is better than the smaller ones they're easier to read. The first few and last few pages seem the weakest in this, so take care in reading.
